es flows naturally from these two assumptions, supporting the idea that phases are indeed a fundamental construct in syntax.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 0aGenerative grammar. 0aGrammar, Comparative and generalxSyntax. 0aMinimalist theory (Linguistics) 0aMinimalist theory (Linguistics). 4aLinguistik. 4aSyntax. 7aFOREIGN LANGUAGE STUDY / English as a Second Language.2bisacsh  aCyclicity.  aLinguistic Theory.  aMinimalism.  aPhases.  aSyntactic Theory.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1z978311023857008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Linguistics and Semiotics  2000-2014 (EN)z978311023845708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Linguistics and Semiotics 2000 - 2014z9783110636970oZDB-23-DLS08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2012z9783110288995oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PACKAGE ENGLISH LINGUISTICS AND LITERATURE 2012z978311028890208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET LINGUISTIK UND LITERATURWISSENSCHAFT  2012z9783110288896oZDB-23-DGA0 cprintz978311028405840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311028422540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110284225423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110284225/original  a978-3-11-023845-7  DGBA Backlist Linguistics and Semiotics  2000-2014 (EN)c2000d2014  a978-3-11-023857-0  DGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1c2000d2014  a978-3-11-028890-2  E-BOOK PACKAGE ENGLISH LINGUISTICS AND LITERATURE 2012b2012  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  a